==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Letch
<hw>Letch</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Lech</er>,
<er>Lecher</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Strong desire; passion;
especially, lust.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some people have a <qex>letch</qex> for unmasking impostors, or
for avenging the wrongs of others.</q> <rj><qau>De
Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A <er>lecher</er>.</def> <mark>[slang]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Letchy</ent>⟦br⟧
